title: Live coverage: SpaceX to launch 23 Starlink satellites on Falcon 9 rocket from Vandenberg Space Force Base
summary: The launch comes following a scrub for weather of the NG-21 mission at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station. Liftoff of the Starlink 11-1 mission is targeting 12:24 a.m. PDT (3:24 a.m. EDT, 0724 UTC) from Space Launch Complex 4 East (SLC-4E).
